text.en_US: Well, I WANTED to make a better version of the training room from the basement of Rhombus Arena.\. This one would have had the elemental lines on the ground change in real time with the player's element.
HOWEVER!\. There is some bizarre code interaction preventing the \c[3]ObjectlayerView\c[0] from checking its \c[3]spawnCondition\c[0] in real time.

Because of this, I can't make the floor lines update when the player swaps elements.\. It's weird because other entities, such as \c[3]EventTrigger\c[0] can detect it in real-time just fine.\. Swap to the \c[2]WAVE\c[0] element and note that the event detects it immediately.

For whatever bizarre reason, the floor lines only update when you begin/end practice using the sign on the right side of this platform.\. I have no idea why this is the case.\. But go ahead, swap elements and then enable/disable the practice to see it.
So anyway, it turns out this map idea won't work out after all.
